body: "Repro: 'pm context --json --max-items 5' -> unknown_option; examples only suggest pm context --help.\n\nWhy it matters: project management = context management — agents reason in 'max items / top N' terms when bounding token spend, and every failed guess costs a help round-trip. This is the same recovery-hint class as GH-458 (pm-qfte, shipped: lifecycle --assignee alias) and generalizes under pm-gdi7 (unknown-option errors should suggest valid flags). If pm-gdi7's generalized did-you-mean suggestion engine lands first, this item reduces to a targeted test case plus the alias decision.\n\nDuplicate-check evidence: pm search 'GH-476' -> 0 hits; pm search 'context row limit aliases' -> no open coverage; pm-gdi7 covers the generic suggestion engine but not this specific alias/hint."
